# Password Generator 🔐

[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](LICENSE) [![Version](https://img.shields.io/badge/version-1.0.0-blue.svg)]()

Secure, customizable password creation—available as a REST API and a React web app.

---

## 📺 Live Demo

🔗 https://password-generator-lime-five-20.vercel.app

---

## ✨ Features

- **Randomized Strength**  
  Mix uppercase, lowercase, numbers & symbols  
- **Custom Length**  
  Choose between 6–32 characters  
- **Toggleable Options**  
  Enable/disable any character type  
- **REST API**  
  `GET /api/generate?length=16&upper=true&lower=true&numbers=true&symbols=true`  
- **Responsive UI**  
  Modern React + TypeScript frontend  

---

## 🚀 Tech Stack

| Layer      | Technology               |
| ---------- | ------------------------ |
| **Backend**| Node.js, Express, TypeScript |
| **Frontend**| React, TypeScript, CSS    |
| **Deploy** | Vercel (frontend) / Your choice (backend) |

---

## 🛠️ Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- **Node.js** ≥ v14  
- **npm** or **yarn**

### Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Kash1shTyagi/Password-Generator.git
cd Password-Generator
````

Install dependencies:

```bash
# Backend
cd backend && npm install

# Frontend
cd ../frontend && npm install
```

### Running Locally

```bash
# Start backend (defaults to port 4000)
cd backend && npm run dev

# Start frontend (defaults to port 3000)
cd frontend && npm start
```

Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) in your browser.

---

## 📖 Usage

### Web UI

1. Adjust sliders & toggles
2. Click **Generate**
3. Copy your secure password

### REST API

```http
GET http://localhost:4000/api/generate
?length=16
&upper=true
&lower=true
&numbers=true
&symbols=true
```

**Response**

```json
{
  "password": "aB3$dF7!GhIjK9Lm"
}
```

